Interactive Use of nprcmanager

library(nprcmanager)
library(stringi)
library(ggplot2)
library(knitr)
library(rmsutilityr)

You can use a file browser

pedigreeFile <- file.choose()

You can point to a pedigree file that you have

pedigreeFile <- "baboon_breeders_qc_ped.csv"

sep <- ","
minParentAge <- 0
breederPedCsv <- read.table(pedigreeFile, sep = sep, header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
breederPed <- qcStudbook(breederPedCsv, minParentAge)

If qcStudbook reports and error, change the call by adding the errors argument set to TRUE and examine the returned object.

badPedigreeFile <- "pedigree_files_with_errors/Pedigree_File_Example_CSV.csv"

ped <- resetPopulation(breederPed, NULL)
probands <- ped$id[ped$population]

                    addBackParents = FALSE)

To use the findLoops function run the following code and select a pedigree as your input file that has a loop in it. I have used the example pedigree that comes with the software Example_Pedigree.csv.

##pedigreeFile <- file.choose() ## use example file
pedigreefile <- pedigreeFile <- "Example_Pedigree.csv"
examplePedigree_raw <- read.table(pedigreeFile, sep = ",", header = TRUE, 
                                   stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
errorLst <- qcStudbook(examplePedigree_raw, minParentAge = 0, errors = TRUE)
print(stri_c("Non-female dams: ", get_and_or_list(errorLst$maleDams), 
             ". These happen to be classified as hermaphrodites."))
## [1] "Non-female dams: 695, 698, and 702. These happen to be classified as hermaphrodites."
examplePedigree <- qcStudbook(examplePedigree_raw, minParentAge = 0)
exampleTree <- createPedTree(examplePedigree)
exampleLoops <- findLoops(exampleTree)

You can count how many loops you have with the following codel

length(exampleLoops[exampleLoops == TRUE])
## [1] 145
nLoops <- countLoops(exampleLoops, exampleTree)
sum(unlist(nLoops[nLoops > 0]))
## [1] 258

You can list the first 10 sets of ids, sires and dams in loops with the following line of code:

examplePedigree[exampleLoops == TRUE, c("id", "sire", "dam")][1:10, ]
